---
description: Database schema design standards for maintainable and performant schemas
alwaysApply: true
---

schema-standards:

- Use snake_case for all table and column names
- Every table must have a primary key (prefer UUID or BIGSERIAL)
- Always add created_at and updated_at timestamp columns
- Use foreign key constraints to enforce referential integrity
- Never store comma-separated values in a single column (violates 1NF)
- Avoid EAV (Entity-Attribute-Value) patterns - use JSONB for flexible attributes
- Index all foreign key columns and frequently queried columns
- Use NOT NULL constraints wherever possible - avoid nullable columns unless truly optional
- Prefix junction/join tables with both entity names (e.g., user_roles, post_tags)
